Od6oHVOh3Y.name: room 3 corpse 1
Od6oHVOh3Y.message:
THIS IS FIRST OFFICER MACMILLION. IT’S TOO LATE… IT’S ALL TOO LATE… BUT… I AM PLEASED TO KNOW THAT I DID MY BEST… THAT’S ALL WE CAN EVER ASK FOR, ISN’T IT? TO MY FAMILY. I LOVE YOU…

- FINAL LOG OF J. MACMILLION. FIRST OFFICER. REGISTRATION NUMBER: 2

ORd2qBtQul.name: room 1 audio box
ORd2qBtQul.message:
“This is the Achilles VII AI, ROGER, I came online when the crew’s vitals disappeared.

I removed you passengers from Cryostasis to help with the ship repairs. We’re in bad shape. Navigation controls are locked-in and I can’t override them. You can, though!

First things first. you will have to activate the emergency power. Look for crew codes."

GTAm7rnCWE.name: room 3 corpse 2
GTAm7rnCWE.message:
MAC HAS JUST PASSED… I’M CERTAIN I’LL BE NEXT… IT’S SUCH A SHAME, YOU KNOW? WE WERE TRYING FOR THE STARS AND AIMING FOR NEW WORLDS… AND THIS… THIS IS WHAT WE GET FOR THAT ENDURANCE AND BRAVERY. BUT THIS DECISION IS THE RIGHT ONE. I’M PROUD OF US FOR MAKING THE TOUGH CALL… I JUST HOPE, SOMEDAY, PEOPLE WILL UNDERSTAND.

- FINAL LOG OF K. CRESCENT. THIRD OFFICER. REGISTRATION NUMBER: 9

lzoeE5QYJy.name: room 6 corpse
lzoeE5QYJy.message:
DO NOT JUMP TO FTL! DO NOT ATTEMPT TO MAKE THE CROSSING!

THERE’S… SOMETHING INSIDE THE HYPERLANE! IT ATTACHED ITSELF TO THE SHIP! IT THREW US OUT OF THE OUR NAVIGATION CORRIDOR! IT’S… MANAGED TO GET INSIDE! WE'VE LOCKED IT INSIDE THE ENGINEERING BAY AS WE…

AoIVAqszaK.name: room 6 command terminal - engine fail
AoIVAqszaK.message:
Initiating FTL travel....
%br%
Engine failed!
%br%
Anomaly detected in the hallway

bDQR4zYpje.name: room 6 captain's last warning
bDQR4zYpje.message:
DO NOT ALLOW THE SHIP TO RETURN TO EARTH!

IF, SOMEHOW, YOU HAVE FOUND THIS TRANSMISSION… PLEASE KNOW THAT THE SHIP HAS SOME FORM OF INFECTION ON BOARD. WE TRIED TO STOP IT. WE COULDN’T. WE ATTEMPTED TO PILOT THE SHIP INTO A BLACK HOLE TO RID THE UNIVERSE OF THIS MENACE!

BUT, PERHAPS YOU HAD INFORMATION WE DID NOT. PERHAPS YOU KNOW WHAT YOU’RE DOING…

BUT MAYBE… YOU ARE INFECTED YOURSELF…

OR ONE OF YOUR TEAM MEMBERS IS…

V5HMYZG3ao.name: voting
V5HMYZG3ao.message:
What should we do?
(Careful, you cannot change your vote)

uefFslrsfH.name: vote ending - blackhole
uefFslrsfH.message:
The Achilles VII's engines come alive and push forward towards a haloed glow spiraling into an incomprehensible absence in space.

The Black Hole beckons you into its maw.

You look at each other and sense both the imminence of your end and the satisfaction of knowing your choice does not bring down doom upon others. The ship creaks and the metal screams as the gravity of your situation becomes... more prominent.

Time, too, rips at its edges, exposing something different beneath.

And as you sail into the true unknown there is a tranquility that unifies you. What comes next cannot be expressed or described. But there is no pain, not really.

Only peace.

And with that, you end.

Iha3AQ3b2z.name: vote ending - earth
Iha3AQ3b2z.message:
The Achilles VII's FTL drive powers up and bores a hole from its current position back to the Earth. Ripping at the fabric of reality itself. Folding inward, the ship vanishes from its position. A spectacular display of science flows within each and every atom as physics warps and shifts; ebbs and flows, and... that's when you hear it. Something has affixed itself to the exterior of the ship. And then another something, and another. Your team share fearful expressions but... before you can make a decision... the journey ends and you emerge at your origin point. The blue and green planet ahead of you. Innocent and ignorant.

The creatures, their anatomy not of this realm, phase through the hull of the ship.

And even as you scream, they enter each and every one of you.

What was you is now only them.

The radio crackles to life, "Achilles VII, we're getting abnormal readings here. Let's get you back on land. We are eager to hear about your trip."

Autopilot engaged. Landing trajectory locked-in.

You bring them their end.

m75FcIPIqp.name: alien recording
m75FcIPIqp.message:
I DO NOT MEAN YOU HARM! I DO NOT MEAN YOU HARM! YOUR SHIP COLLIDED WITH MINE WITHIN THE FOLD AND I HAD TO ESCAPE TO YOURS TO SURVIVE! I’M TRYING TO MAKE YOU UNDERSTAND.

I’M TRYING TO MAKE YOU KNOW THAT I AM NOT YOUR ENEMY. PLEASE! I DO NOT WANT TO DEFEND MYSELF. I DO NOT WANT TO HURT YOU!

PLEASE. PLEASE. I JUST WANT TO GET HOME TO MY FAMILY. MY CHILDREN. MY PEOPLE.

PLEASE… PLEASE DO NOT HURT ME…

eKPtvNnnRP.name: intro
eKPtvNnnRP.message:
ENTERING THE EXPERIMENTAL DEEPSTRING-FOLD LEADING FROM EARTH TO THE TEEGARDEN STAR, THE ACHILLES VII, A PROTOTYPE SPACESHIP, HAS BEEN HIT BY A WAVE OF EXOTIC MATTER, EXPOSING ALL THOSE NOT IN CRYOSTASIS TO AN UNKNOWN CONTAMINATION.

AND… ALONG WITH THIS… SOMETHING SOLID HAS DAMAGED THE ACHILLES VII’S HULL, FORCING IT FROM THE FASTER-THAN-LIGHT TRAVEL AND DISABLING THE ONBOARD COMPUTER AND SYSTEMS.

HOURS LATER, AS BACKUP SYSTEMS COME ONLINE, THE REST OF THE CREW AWAKES TO FIND THEMSELVES BLIND TO THEIR SITUATION…

TIME TO INVESTIGATE.

iWLuOxLnOA.name: ending
iWLuOxLnOA.message:
THE JOURNEY TO THE TEEGARDEN STAR MADE FOR A DEADLY FIRST CONTACT WITH AN ADVANCED ALIEN SPECIES.

WITH THE ALIEN NEEDLESSLY DEFEATED, HOWEVER, HUMANITY IS ABOUT TO COME EXPERIENCE SECOND CONTACT AS THE ALIEN’S OWN HOMEWORLD PREPARES TO SEND AN INVESTIGATION CRAFT TO DISCOVER WHAT HAS TRANSPIRED.

THE CREW OF THE ACHILLES VII BELIEVE THEY HAVE SAVED THEMSELVES FROM A MONSTER.

BUT, AS TIME OFTEN TELLS, IT IS THE FEAR OF THE OTHER THAT PROVES HUMANITY IS THE TRUE MONSTER, AFTER ALL.

WHAT LIES AHEAD, IS UNCERTAIN.

RETRIBUTION. REVENGE. WAR.

PERHAPS, EVEN, PEACE, IF WE CAN ONLY ALLOW THE OPPORTUNITY.
